title: HTML5 eBooks Collection 2013 Edition [PDF].zip
description:
HTML5 eBooks Collection 
English | 96 Books | PDF | Large Books Collection | 1.41 GB 
Genre: Web Design, Developers, Programming


HTML5 is a markup language for structuring and presenting content for the World Wide Web and a core technology of the Internet. It is the fifth revision of the HTML standard (created in 1990 and standardized as HTML4 as of 1997) and, as of December 2012, is a W3C Candidate Recommendation. Its core aims have been to improve the language with support for the latest multimedia while keeping it easily readable by humans and consistently understood by computers and devices (web browsers, parsers, etc.). HTML5 is intended to subsume not only HTML 4, but XHTML 1 and DOM Level 2 HTML as well.
